columnOne.description:
16x16inches, acrylic on wood
//
The universe is within us and around us. We can find the whole new galaxy in ourselves. To look at the sky full of stars can be enough for some people to be happy, but sometimes you need to find one star inside of you. Not the kind of star that will make you famous, but the one that will shine bright in the darkest night.

11x14inches, acrylic on wood
//
'Grace comes into the soul, as the morning sun into the world; first a dawning, then a light; and at last the sun in his full and excellent brightness.' - Thomas Adams

36x24inches, oil on canvas
//
A famous Hindu myth about the World Turtle carrying four elephants carrying the Earth is widely known among us. But its nice sometimes to step back and let go the imagination. Just let the turtle flow in the blue abyss of playful colors, carrying our lives on the top of her back. Tortoise carries its millennial wisdom, and we might want to learn a trick or two from her.

16x20inches, acrylic on wood
//
Ability to adapt and change belongs to both chameleons and humans. But don’t forget, that with change of color - we should stay true to our beliefs and values.

10x16inches, acrylic on paper
//
We build our own houses and cities, - ideal and perfect in our head. Its up to us to decide to see in color or in grey tones. My perfect city is full of shades of blue and green, on a cloud where no negativity and rain can reach me and other city’s inhabitants. Going places, guided by wind and sunny weather. Maybe too romantic and too perfect, but its mine. To each its own.

oil on cotton canvas
//
Two color study created during undergrad in fine arts. It means nothing more than shapes and colors, open to all interpretations.

columnTwo.description:
11x14inches, acrylic on wood
//
Growth only occurs in the sate of discomfort. Keep on growing.

24x30, oil on cotton canvas
//
Each of us has a perfect world inside of our heads. Free of fear, lies and pain. Let this world be not only inside you, but outside. Live. Dream.

18x18inches, acrylic on wood
//
It doesn’t matter if you stand on one leg or both. It doesn’t matter if you wear pink, blue or black. Just be yourself and you’ll always stand out as long as you keep your head up.

24x36inches, acrylic on wood
//
See a glass as half full, not half empty. Positive outlook makes people do greater things in life. Strive for more and you will achieve your full greatness.

columnThree.description:
20x24inches, acrylic on wood
//
Saturn is the slowest planet (in orbit around the Sun), but also in Roman mythology - Saturn was a god of time. Time is our most precious thing. Use it wisely as it won’t stop, but will only keep spinning round and round. To spend time with people with whom we don't see a long-term potential is to invest in person who will not be there for you tomorrow.

20x20inches, acrylic on wood
//
The Greek poet Hesiod wrote that snails signified the time to harvest by climbing up the stems. This symbolized growth and rebirth. As women, we lead new innovations and ideas, we build new generations. We constantly grow and climb up the social ladder. Slowly but steady, small but many – may we rise up and carry our future to the brightest point.

11x14inches, acrylic on wood
//
We didn’t get to choose where life planted us. It is our choice, however, how well we bloom.

30x30inches, acrylic on wood
//
Adapting to the environment is not the easiest thing. Fitting into something new, changing shapes and colors quickly, like octopus do, is a great skill to have. While doing so, lets be smart about staying true to ourselves. Don’t let any enemy of the world-sea scare us. But if someone do - spray some ink on them and move on.

10x16inches, acrylic on canvas
//
A gift, Yuliya painted for an amazing photographer, ocean ambassador and a mermaid Kristin Hettermann. Kristin strives to share positive stories, document the earth and its cultures, inspire people to explore, encourage the balance of mind-body-spirit through holistic life practices, and raise awareness for important causes, particularly the protection and restoration of the world’s oceans.

columnFour.description:
11x14inches, acrylic on wood
//
The only way is up.

18x18inches, acrylic on wood
//
We are often caught in the whirl of life, forgetting about colorful beauty of small details that surround us. Be grateful for what you have - your health, your loved ones and yourself. Spreading energy from my atomic world to yours.

oil on cotton canvas
//
A study of Louisa Matthiasdottir's painting. Bright and vivid colors, typical for Matthiasdottir's artworks served as inspiration for some of Yuliya's early works.

oil on cotton canvas
//
Yuliya's first oil artworks, painted when she just moved to New York in 2012.

oil on cotton canvas
//
Two color study created during undergrad year in fine arts.
